Class WorkflowBundle

    Cloneable, Comparable, Revisioned, Named, Root, WorkflowBean

    public class WorkflowBundle
extends AbstractRevisioned
implements WorkflowBean, Named, Root, Revisioned
    A workflow bundle is a collection of workflows, profiles and their annotations.

    A Workflow Bundle represents these resources as a whole, and have its own identifier.

    Workflows are listed under getWorkflows(), one of which SHOULD be setMainWorkflow(Workflow).

    Similarly, profiles are listed under getProfiles(), one of which SHOULD be setMainProfile(Profile).

    Annotations are included under getAnnotations(), and additional resources inside getResources().

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object obj)
        WorkflowBundles are only equal by instance identity.

        Thus, if you load or construct the same workflow bundle twice, say as wb1 and wb2, then wb1.equals(wb2) == false.

        There are two reasons for this. Firstly, a workflow bundle is a complex object, as it bundles not just the getWorkflows() and getProfiles(), but also arbitrary resources in getResources(). Two workflow bundles can for most purposes be assumed "equal" if they have the same identifier in getGlobalBaseURI() - they might however vary in which annotations they carry.

        The second is that applications might use WorkflowBundle instances as keys in a Map of open workflows, and want to distinguish between two workflow bundles from two different (but possibly identical) files; for instance a .t2flow and a .wfbundle.

        Note that contained workflow beans such as Workflow and Activity will likewise not be AbstractNamed.equals(Object) across workflow bundles, as a named bean is considered equal only if its name matches and its parents are (recursively) equal. You may however detach the children by setting their parents to null and check for equality in isolation.
